                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="252775" author="adilger" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2019 18:24:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-455&quot; title=&quot;Document mdt.*.readonly parameter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-455&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-455&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to track the manual additions for this feature.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="251843" author="pjones" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2019 22:05:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We easily can - &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/projects/LUDOC/versions/14590&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://jira.whamcloud.com/projects/LUDOC/versions/14590&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="251840" author="adilger" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2019 21:45:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Peter, we can&apos;t track LUDOC tickets against the 2.13 release in Jira, AFAIK.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="251797" author="pjones" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2019 12:12:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t that be tracked under an LUDOC ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="250779" author="adilger" created="Fri, 5 Jul 2019 20:52:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think there was an update to the manual to document this new functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="241705" author="pjones" created="Mon, 11 Feb 2019 15:09:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.13&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="241677" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 11 Feb 2019 03:21:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg Drokin (green@whamcloud.com) merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33892/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33892/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11811&quot; title=&quot;Provide an interface to set Lustre MDT into readonly mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; mdt: Add a proc entry to set MDT to readonly&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 23bae7dc21b5c955c096431d485e49a7298ec404&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="238818" author="adilger" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2018 05:39:46 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;pdsh &amp;#45;w mgs_server &quot;lctl &amp;#42;.&amp;#42;.$FSNAME&amp;#42;&amp;#45;.active=0&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this would make a difference?  While it would make the OSTs inactive on the MGS (or maybe the MDS also, if they are the same machine), this would only stop the &lt;em&gt;objects&lt;/em&gt; from being destroyed.  It wouldn&apos;t stop the MDS from deleting the filenames from the filesystem, including the layout xattrs, and the pending-unlink OST objects would mostly be useless even if the data is still on the OSTs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="238812" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 18 Dec 2018 23:46:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jinshan Xiong (jinshan.xiong@gmail.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33892&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33892&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
